{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.1",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 1 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:1",
      "text": "The proverbs of Solomon, son of David, king of Israel:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:2",
      "text": "That men may know wisdom and instruction, understand words of insight,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:3",
      "text": "receive instruction in wise dealing, righteousness, justice, and equity;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:4",
      "text": "that prudence may be given to the simple, knowledge and discretion to the youth—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:5",
      "text": "the wise man also may hear and increase in learning, and the man of understanding acquire skill,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:6",
      "text": "to understand a proverb and a figure, the words of the wise and their riddles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:7",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge; fools despise wisdom and instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:8",
      "text": "Hear, my son, your father's instruction, and reject not your mother's teaching;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:9",
      "text": "for they are a fair garland for your head, and pendants for your neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:10",
      "text": "My son, if sinners entice you, do not consent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:11",
      "text": "If they say, “Come with us, let us lie in wait for blood, let us wantonly ambush the innocent;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:12",
      "text": "like Sheol let us swallow them alive and whole, like those who go down to the Pit:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:13",
      "text": "we shall find all precious goods, we shall fill our houses with spoil;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:14",
      "text": "throw in your lot among us, we will all have one purse”—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:15",
      "text": "my son, do not walk in the way with them, hold back your foot from their paths;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:16",
      "text": "for their feet run to evil, and they make haste to shed blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:17",
      "text": "For in vain is a net spread in the sight of any bird;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:18",
      "text": "but these men lie in wait for their own blood, they set an ambush for their own lives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:19",
      "text": "Such are the ways of all who get gain by violence; it takes away the life of its possessors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:20",
      "text": "Wisdom cries aloud in the street; in the markets she raises her voice;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:21",
      "text": "on the top of the walls she cries out; at the entrance of the city gates she speaks:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:22",
      "text": "“How long, O simple ones, will you love being simple? How long will scoffers delight in their scoffing and fools hate knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:23",
      "text": "Give heed to my reproof; behold, I will pour out my thoughts to you; I will make my words known to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:24",
      "text": "Because I have called and you refused to listen, have stretched out my hand and no one has heeded,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:25",
      "text": "and you have ignored all my counsel and would have none of my reproof,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:26",
      "text": "I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when panic strikes you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:27",
      "text": "when panic strikes you like a storm, and your calamity comes like a whirlwind, when distress and anguish come upon you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:28",
      "text": "Then they will call upon me, but I will not answer; they will seek me diligently but will not find me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:29",
      "text": "Because they hated knowledge and did not choose the fear of the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:30",
      "text": "would have none of my counsel, and despised all my reproof,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:31",
      "text": "therefore they shall eat the fruit of their way and be sated with their own devices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:32",
      "text": "For the simple are killed by their turning away, and the complacence of fools destroys them;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.1.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:33",
      "text": "but he who listens to me will dwell secure and will be at ease, without dread of evil.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
